In all the orchards, the evaluated trees were identified with ribbons. From the fifth row, counting from the edge, we selected 40 trees/orchard, and from each one, a median branch was collected from which three leaves were detached, one from each stratum of the plant: basal, median and apical. Collections were carried out monthly, totaling 120 leaves/orchard/month. In winter, when apple trees lose their leaves, buds from a median branch of each stratum were evaluated, totalizing 120 buds/orchard/month and 40 for each stratum/orchard/month. The leaves or buds were individualized in plastic bags, and then packed in styrofoam boxes containing artificial ice (Gelo-x 
